               <p>xs:string</p>
            </td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <p>Applies to: XPath 2.0, XSLT 2.0, XQuery 1.0 and later versions</p>
      <p>
            <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xpath-functions/#func-string-join" class="bodylink">XPath 2.0 Specification</a>
         </p>
      <p>
            <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xpath-functions-11/#func-string-join"
            class="bodylink">XPath 3.0 Specification</a>
         </p>
      <p class="subhead">Notes on the Saxon implementation</p>
      <p>The single-argument form of this function is specified in XPath 3.0,
         and is newly supported in Saxon 9.3, provided XPath 3.0 is enabled. Note that
      the default separator is a zero-length string, not a single space.</p>
